0Chicago%20Bears%20Legend%2C%20Dies%20at%2080%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696545504000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FDick-Butkus-Obit-Dead.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D562%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235746755%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dick%20Butkus%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20celebrated%20linebackers%20in%20NFL%20history%20who%20played%20eight%20seasons%20for%20the%20Chicago%20Bears%20before%20turning%20to%20a%20career%20as%20an%20actor%20and%20sports%20commentator%2C%20died%20Thursday%20in%20Malibu.%20He%20was%2080%20years%20old.%20Butkus%E2%80%99%20death%20was%20confirmed%20by%20the%20Chicago%20Tribune.%20A%20Chicago%20native%2C%20Butkus%20was%20drafted%20by%20his%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fobituaries-people-news%2Fdick-butkus-dead-chicago-bears-nfl-1235746755%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fobituaries-people-news%2Fdick-butkus-dead-chicago-bears-nfl-1235746755%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fobituaries-people-news%2Fdick-butkus-dead-chicago-bears-nfl-1235746755%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cannibalistic%20Europeans%20likely%20ate%20their%20dead%20at%20funerals%2015%2C000%20years%20ago%20instead%20of%20burying%20them%2C%20study%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221218%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bone%20from%20the%20Upper%20Palaeolithic%20Era%20engraved%20with%20markings%20associated%20with%20ritual%20cannibalism.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651f2cca6e038039826aec77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22913%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20bone%20from%20the%20Upper%20Paleolithic%20Era%20engraved%20with%20markings%20associated%20with%20ritual%20cannibalism%2C%20from%20London's%20Natural%20History%20Museum%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EEuropeans%20probably%20ate%20their%20dead%20loved%20ones%20instead%20of%20burying%20them%2015%2C000%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAccording%20to%20a%20new%20study%2C%20the%20consumption%20of%20dead%20people%20was%20not%20essential%2C%20but%20a%20ritual.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EResearchers%20also%20said%20people%20used%20the%20remaining%20bones%20as%20cups%20and%20chewed%20on%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECannibalistic%20Europeans%20likely%20feasted%20on%20their%20deceased%20loved%20ones%20at%20funerals%20instead%20of%20burying%20them%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20now%20believe%20that%20cannibalism%20was%20widespread%20among%20Magdalenian%20Upper%20Palaeolithic%20people%2C%20who%20lived%20across%20Europe%20between%2011%2C000%20and%2017%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study%20published%20in%20Quaternary%20Science%20Reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study's%20researchers%20analyzed%20funerary%20practices%20at%2025%20Magdalenians%20burial%20sites%20across%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Spain%2C%20Russia%2C%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20Belgium%2C%20Poland%2C%20the%20Czech%20Republic%2C%20and%20Portugal.%20The%20study%20found%20evidence%20that%20these%20early%20humans%20had%20chew%20marks%20on%20their%20dead's%20bones%2C%20used%20their%20skulls%20as%20cups%2C%20and%20extracted%20bone%20marrow%20from%20the%20bodies%20for%20nutrients.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20ancient%20humans%20appeared%20to%20have%20combined%20the%20human%20remains%20with%20animal%20remains%2C%20per%20the%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20had%20previously%20known%20of%20a%20few%20instances%20of%20cannibalism%20among%20this%20group%2C%20like%20those%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhm.ac.uk%2Fdiscover%2Fthe-cannibals-of-goughs-cave.html%5C%22%3EGough's%20Cave%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20skull%20cups%20and%20other%20human%20bones%20were%20found%2C%20but%20had%20not%20known%20until%20now%20just%20how%20commonplace%20the%20practice%20was.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20wrote%20that%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bundeniable%20that%20the%20frequency%20of%20cannibalistic%20cases%20among%20Magdalenian%20sites%20exceeds%20any%20incidence%20of%20this%20behaviour%20among%20earlier%20or%20later%20hominin%20groups%2C%20and%20suggests%20that%20mortuary%20cannibalism%20was%20a%20method%20Magdalenian%20people%20used%20to%20dispose%20of%20their%20deceased.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Silvia%20Bello%2C%20a%20paleoanthropologist%20and%20co-author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhm.ac.uk%2Fpress-office%2Fpress-releases%2FARCHAEOLOGICAL-ANALYSIS-IDENTIFIES-OLDEST-EVIDENCE-OF-CANNIBALISM-AS-A-FUNERARY-PRACTICE.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20cannibalistic%20behavior%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20simply%20practiced%20out%20of%20necessity%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20rather%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bfunerary%20practice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudy%20co-author%20Dr.%20William%20Marsh%20added%20that%20their%20findings%20offered%20a%20contextualization%20of%20Gough's%20Cave.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20terminal%20time%20period%20of%20the%20Palaeolithic%2C%20you%20actually%20see%20a%20turnover%20in%20both%20genetic%20ancestry%20and%20funerary%20behaviour%2C%20indicative%20of%20population%20replacement%20as%20Epigravettian%20groups%20migrated%20northwards%2C%26quot%3B%20Marsh%20said%20in%20the%20release.%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20the%20change%20in%20funerary%20behaviour%20identified%20here%20is%20an%20example%20of%20demic%20diffusion%20where%20essentially%20one%20population%20comes%20in%20and%20replaces%20another%20population%20and%20that%20brings%20about%20a%20change%20in%20behaviour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20of%20the%20study%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20for%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcannibalistic-europeans-ate-dead-funerals-ritual-burial-palaeolithic-era-magdalenian-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696545308000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651f2cca6e038039826aec77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcannibalistic-europeans-ate-dead-funerals-ritual-burial-palaeolithic-era-magdalenian-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20now%20think%20cannibalism%20was%20common%20among%20Magdalenian%20Upper%20Palaeolithic%20people%2C%20who%20lived%20across%20Europe%20between%2011%2C000%20and%2017%2C000%20years%20ago.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Sebastian%20Cahill%2CGrace%20Eliza%20Goodwin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcannibalistic-europeans-ate-dead-funerals-ritual-burial-palaeolithic-era-magdalenian-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Protesters%20angry%20about%20Ramaswamy's%20Ukraine%20aid%20comments%20strike%20his%20empty%20car%20in%20Iowa%2C%20campaign%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696545171000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104197943%2Cimgsize-895414.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fprotesters-angry-about-ramaswamys-ukraine-aid-comments-strike-his-empty-car-in-iowa-campaign-says%2Farticleshow%2F104197795.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104197795.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EProtesters%20in%20Iowa%20confronted%20presidential%20can