nds.%20%26quot%3BThe%20panic%20attack%20came%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20because%20%5Binvestors%5D%20essentially%20found%20that%20the%20Fed%20was%20not%20responding%20to%20the%20increase%20in%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20suddenly%20they%20piled%20on%20each%20other%20to%20sell%20the%20bonds.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ESevered%20from%20fundamentals%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20also%20possible%20that%20the%20surge%20in%20bond%20yields%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-fundstrat-rally-fed-rates-inflation-bond-yields-2023-10%3F_gl%3D1*41thiv*_ga*MjMxMzA1Mzg2LjE2NTY0NDQxNTU.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5NjUxODkzOC43MTMuMS4xNjk2NTIwMzg4LjU2LjAuMA..%5C%22%3Edisconnected%20from%20some%20fundamentals%20of%20the%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20US%20debt%20balance%2C%20for%20one%2C%20has%20worried%20economists%20for%20years%2C%20and%20markets%20have%20been%20eyeing%20a%20possible%20recession%20since%20early%202022%2C%20meaning%20none%20of%20the%20fears%20investors%20appear%20to%20be%20responding%20to%20in%20the%20last%20month%20are%20new%20or%20unfamiliar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20though%20the%20US%2010-year%20bond%20yield%20is%20higher%20than%20that%20of%20other%20countries%2C%20like%20Spain%20or%20Germany%2C%20US%20inflation%20is%20lower%20by%20comparison%2C%20Fundstrat's%20Tom%20Lee%20notes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20maybe%20this%20is%20another%20example%20of%20how%20there's%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20momentum%20pushing%20yields%20higher%2C%20but%20it%20may%20be%20divorced%20from%20fundamentals%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said%20in%20a%20video%20to%20Fundstrat%20clients%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20rates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20stay%20high%20for%20this%20long%2C%20he%20added%2C%20especially%20when%20looking%20at%20cooling%20inflation%20indicators.%20By%20some%20measures%E2%80%94like%20shelter%20prices%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2