ul%3E%20%3Cli%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20House%20elected%20to%20remove%20Rep.%20Kevin%20McCarthy%20from%20his%20role%20as%20speaker.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAnd%20while%20a%20handful%20of%20members%20are%20calling%20for%20a%20Trump%20speakership%2C%20there's%20no%20shot%20of%20it%20happening.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EA%20non-member%20has%20never%20been%20speaker%2C%20and%20GOP%20conference%20rules%20appear%20to%20stand%20in%20Trump's%20way.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20only%20been%20two%20days%20since%20a%20majority%20of%20members%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20elected%20to%20boot%20GOP%20Rep.%20Kevin%20McCarthy%20from%20the%20speakership%2C%20but%20a%20select%20few%20have%20already%20said%20they've%20settled%20on%20a%20replacement.%20Specifically%2C%20one%20that%20has%20a%20lower%20chance%20of%20happening%20than%20Sen.%20John%20Fetterman%20becoming%20an%20avid%20fan%20of%20men's%20formal%20wear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20Republican%20bomb-thrower%20Rep.%20Marjorie%20Taylor%20Greene%2C%20Rep.%20Greg%20Steube%2C%20and%20Rep.%20Troy%20Nehls%20have%20each%20publicly%20stated%20they%20want%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20to%20be%20led%20for%20the%20next%20year%20by%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRepMTG%2Fstatus%2F1709397608576266457%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreene%20going%20as%20far%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20say%20that%20he's%20the%20%26quot%3Bonly%20candidate%26quot%3B%20for%20speaker%20she's%20currently%20down%20to%20vote%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20technically%20legal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20can%20technically%20successfully%20get%20elected%20as%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20%E2%80%94%20yes%2C%20non-members%20of%20Congress%20can%20as%20well%20due%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2F10%2F04%2Fhouse-speaker-replacement%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BAir%20Bud%26quot%3B-esque%3C%2Fa%3E%20lack%20of%20regulation%20around%20who%20can%20fill%20the%20position%20to%20begin%20with%20%E2%80%94%20but%20in%20more%20than%20200%20years%20of%20congressional%20sessions%20and%20speakerships%2C%20there%20hasn't%20once%20been%20a%20non-sitting%20member%20of%20the%20House%20chosen%20as%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20Republicans%20in%20the%20House%20hold%20such%20a%20narrow%20majority%2C%20there's%20also%20practically%20no%20possibility%20of%20Trump%20becoming%20speaker%20if%20only%20a%20few%20GOP%20members%20are%20opposed%2C%20as%20there's%20zero%20chance%20even%20a%20single%20Democrat%20would%20vote%20for%20the%20embattled%20former%20president%20to%20lead%20the%20chamber.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20moment%2C%20there's%20also%20no%20assurance%20that%20Trump%20is%20even%20interested%20in%20the%20position%20at%20all.%20Speaking%20to%20reporters%20at%20his%20civil%20fraud%20trial%20in%20New%20York%2C%20he%20recently%20said%20his%20focus%20was%20%26quot%3Btotally%20on%26quot%3B%20running%20for%20president%2C%20though%20he%20also%20noted%20he'd%20%26quot%3Bdo%20whatever%20is%20best%20for%20the%20country%20and%20for%20the%20Republican%20Party.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20he%20gets%20immense%20GOP%20congressional%20support%20to%20become%20speaker%2C%20Trump%20also%20appears%20like%20the%20very%20last%20person%20who'd%20even%20want%20the%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllow%20me%20to%20explain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%20angry%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651f03ea9f7ca8b2bbdabcd6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20speaks%20in%20the%20Brady%20Briefing%20Room%20at%20the%20White%20House%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%20on%20November%205%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20BRENDAN%20SMIALOWSKI%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThis%20job%20is%20all%20the%20things%20Donald%20Trump%20dislikes%20about%20power%20and%20none%20of%20the%20things%20he%20likes%20about%20being%20powerful%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20holding%20immense%20authority%20in%20the%20US%20government%2C%20and%20joining%20the%20upper%20rungs%20of%20the%20presidential%20line%20of%20succession%2C%20the%20roles%20of%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20and%20president%20are%20wildly%20different.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20president%2C%20Trump%20was%20free%20to%20hire%20and%20fire%20staffers%2C%20counsel%2C%20and%20his%20cabinet%20at%20any%20point%20he%20wanted.%20With%20that%20power%2C%20the%20former%20president%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Ftracking-turnover-in-the-trump-administration%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecycled%20through%3C%2Fa%3E%20chiefs%20of%20staff%2C%20agency%20directors%2C%20and%20more%20during%20his%20four%20years%20in%20office%20despite%20stating%20before%20becoming%20president%20that%20he'd%20surround%20himself%20with%20only%20%26quot%3Bthe%20best%20and%20most%20serious%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20he%20becomes%20speaker%2C%20he'd%20still%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20dismiss%20a%20member%20of%20the%20speaker's%20office%20staff%20if%20upset%20with%20them%2C%20but%20he%20wouldn't%20have%20the%20power%20to%20remove%20the%20peskiest%20people%20he'd%20run%20into%20on%20the%20job%3A%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20representatives%20themselves%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20publicly%20denigrating%20any%20politician%20who%20acts%20out%20of%20sync%20with%20what%20he%20personally%20wants%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20shame%20them%20into%20falling%20in%20line.%20If%20he%20continued%20to%20go%20after%20members%20like%20that%20as%20speaker%20instead%20of%20trying%20to%20mend%20relationships%20and%20make%20concessions%2C%20it'd%20be%20hard%20for%20him%20to%20find%20much%20success%20in%20the%20role%20and%20pass%20the%20necessary%20legislation%20to%20keep%20the%20government%20funded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20speaker%20but%20not%20a%20member%20of%20Congress%2C%20Trump%20would%20have%20literally%20no%20ability%20to%20vote%20on%20any%20pieces%20of%20legislation.%20And%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsgp.fas.org%2Fcrs%2Fmisc%2F97-780.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecenturies%20of%20tradition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he'd%20also%20be%20discouraged%20from%20voicing%20his%20opinion%20during%20floor%20debates%20and%20would%20be%20required%20to%20intimately%20learn%20the%20customary%20parliamentary%20procedure%20necessary%20to%20keep%20such%20a%20massive%20legislative%20body%20in%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trump%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651f04916561dd877e71f4fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20signs%20autographs%20outside%20a%20Carvel%20Ice%20Cream%20and%20Cake%20Shop%20during%20the%20California%20GOP%20convention%20on%20September%2029%2C%202023%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California.%3Cp%3EDavid%20McNew%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ELet's%20say%20Trump%20is%20fine%20with%20that.%20Can%20he%20even%20get%20the%20job%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20imagine%2C%20for%20a%20minute%2C%20that%20Trump's%20both%20interested%20in%20the%20position%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20somehow%20manage%20to%20convince%20GOP%20members%20to%20take%20McCarthy's%20spot.%20There'd%20still%20be%20one%20major%20obstacle%20for%20him%20to%20overcome%3A%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gop.gov%2Fconference-rules-of-the-118th-congress%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublican%20conference's%3C%2Fa%3E%20own%20rules%20for%20this%20session%20of%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Democratic%20Rep.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FSeanCasten%2Fstatus%2F1709387209449632218%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESean%20Casten%3C%2Fa%3E%20pointed%20out%20Tuesday%20night%2C%20rule%2026(a)%20states%20that%20%26quot%3BA%20member%20of%20the%20Republican%20Leadership%20shall%20step%20aside%20if%20indicted%20for%20a%20felony%20for%20which%20a%20sentence%20of%20two%20or%20more%20years%20imprisonment%20may%20be%20imposed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%20alone%2C%20federal%20and%20state%20grand%20juries%20have%20thrown%20the%20book%20at%20Trump%20over%20allegations%20of%20business%20fraud%2C%20attempting%20to%20overturn%20the%20results%20of%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%2C%20used%20a%20%26quot%3Bhush%20money%26quot%3B%20scheme%20to%20pay%20off%20a%20porn%20star%2C%20and%20mishandling%20classified%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20he's%20been%20charged%20with%2091%20felony%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20GOP%20conference's%20own%20rules%2C%20however%2C%20already%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20circumvented%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20former%20Speaker%20Newt%20Gingrich%20angrily%20pointed%20out%20in%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fopinions%2F2023%2F10%2F03%2Fnewt-gingrich-matt-gaetz-remove%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeditorial%20piece%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20rules%20stipulate%20that%20the%20ability%20for%20a%20member%20to%20file%20a%20motion%20to%20vacate%20%26quot%3Bshould%20only%20be%20available%20with%20the%20agreement%20of%20the%20Republican%20Conference%20so%20as%20to%20not%20allow%20Democrats%20to%20choose%20the%20Speaker.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20yes%2C%20just%20as%20a%20well-trained%20golden%20retriever%20could%20theoretically%20lead%20the%20House%2C%20so%20too%20could%20Trump%20if%20he%20can%20unite%20the%20conference%20and%20sidestep%20its%20own%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20obstacle%20after%20obstacle%20in%20the%20way%2C%20and%20the%20position%20likely%20not%20even%20personally%20interesting%20to%20Trump%2C%20it's%20probably%20best%20for%20Congress%20to%20look%20elsewhere%20for%20a%20new%20leader.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20obviously%20enjoys%20being%20a%20speaker.%20But%20can%20he%20tolerate%20having%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20House%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-expect-trump-to-become-house-speaker-anytime-soon-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696532578000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ee48f6561dd877e71aa45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-expect-trump-to-become-house-speaker-anytime-soon-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20non-member%20has%20never%20been%20speaker%2C%20and%20GOP%20conference%20rules%20appear%20to%20stand%20in%20Trump's%20way.%20He'd%20also%20have%20no%20ability%20to%20vote%20on%20legislation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mhall%40businessinsider.com%20(Madison%20Hall)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A107%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdont-expect-trump-to-become-house-speaker-anytime-soon-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20shoots%20down%20armed%20Turkish%20drone%20after%20it%20came%20too%20close%20to%20US%20troops%20in%20Syria%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696532438000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104195954%2Cimgsize-173278.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-shoots-down-armed-turkish-drone-after-it-came-too-close-to-us-troops-in-syria%2Farticleshow%2F104195921.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104195