%20got%20smaller%2C%20according%20to%20Mohamed%20El-Erian.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20top%20economist%20pointed%20to%20two%20trends%20that%20could%20help%20push%20the%20economy%20into%20a%20downturn.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20New%20York%20Fed%20has%20priced%20in%20a%2056%25%20chance%20of%20a%20recession%20happening%20by%20September%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20reasons%20why%20America's%20odds%20of%20avoiding%20a%20recession%20may%20be%20dwindling%2C%20according%20to%20top%20economist%20Mohamed%20El-Erian.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Allianz%20chief%20economic%20adviser%20has%20repeatedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-federal-reserve-inflation-hikes-mohamed-el-erian-2022-12%5C%22%3Esounded%20the%20alarm%20for%20a%20coming%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202022%2C%20the%20year%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20began%20to%20aggressively%20raise%20interest%20rates%20to%20fight%20inflation.%20Then%2C%20prices%20in%20the%20economy%20began%20to%20cool%2C%20fueling%20hope%20that%20central%20bankers%20could%20possibly%20steer%20the%20economy%20into%20a%20soft-landing%20and%20get%20inflation%20under%20control%20without%20having%20to%20spark%20a%20damaging%20recession.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20downturn%20has%20edged%20up%2C%20El-Erian%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F02a899eb-e899-4b6f-8848-b5240a7127e9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20an%20op-ed%20for%20the%20Financial%20Times%20on%20Thursday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20there%20are%20two%20factors%20that%20could%20spark%20a%20downturn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20An%20%26quot%3Bintense%26quot%3B%20period%20of%20rising%20rates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed's%20interest%20rate%20hikes%20have%20steadily%20pushed%20up%20borrowing%20costs%20and%20are%20causing%20pain%20all%20over%20the%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ffinancial-crisis-stock-market-crash-bonds-10-year-treasury-jpmorgan-2023-10%5C%22%3EYields%20on%20the%2010-year%20US%20Treasury%20bond%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20jumped%20an%20%26quot%3Beye-popping%26quot%3B%20percentage%20point%20since%20the%20end%20of%20the%20June%2C%20El-Erian%20said%2C%20which%20has%20hiked%20the%20cost%20of%20borrowing%20for%20companies%20and%20households.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-mortgage-refinance-rates-today-friday-29-2023-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMortgage%2520rates%2520are%2520officially%2520the%2Cweek%252C%2520according%2520to%2520Freddie%2520Mac.%5C%22%3EMortgage%20rates%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20just%20notched%20a%2023-year%20high%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20are%20edging%20closer%20to%208%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20yields%20have%20also%20added%20strain%20to%20the%20banking%20sector%2C%20as%20more%20investors%20are%20reallocating%20their%20cash%20to%20money%20market%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20well%20over%20a%20year%20now%2C%20I%20have%20argued%20that%20the%20US%20is%20able%20to%20avoid%20the%202023%20recession%20that%20many%20were%20repeatedly%20calling.%20I%20am%20now%20less%20confident%20about%20what's%20in%20store%20for%202024%20given%20how%20the%20recent%20surge%20in%20rates%20compounds%20the%20erosion%20in%20financial%2C%20human%20and%20institutional%20resilience%2C%26quot%3B%20El-Erian%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Resurgent%20inflation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EInflation%20has%20cooled%20considerably%20from%20its%20highs%20last%20summer%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20chance%20it%20could%20still%20rebound%20as%20price%20pressures%20remain%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInflation%20re-accelerated%20in%20August%20to%203.7%25%20year-over-year%2C%20higher%20than%20the%203.2%25%20reported%20in%20July.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAdding%20fuel%20to%20this%20fire%20are%20high%20prices%20for%20oil%2