based%20on%20the%20presumption%20that%20Indian%20troops%20were%20active%20in%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20victory%2C%20Muizzu%20had%20reiterated%20that%20his%20administration%20would%20commence%20work%20on%20removing%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20from%20the%20first%20day%20of%20his%20job.%20His%20presidential%20term%20will%20be%20inaugurated%20on%20November%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20weekly%20media%20briefing%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20Arindam%20Bagchi%2C%20answering%20questions%20about%20the%20new%20Maldives%20President-elect%E2%80%99s%20statements%20on%20Indian%20troops%2C%20said%20that%20there%20was%20need%20to%20work%20closely%20on%20regional%20security%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20I%20would%20say%E2%80%A6%20the%20focus%20of%20our%20partnership%20with%20the%20Maldives%20has%20always%20been%20on%20capacity%20building%20and%20working%20together%20to%20address%20our%20shared%20challenges%20and%20priorities%2C%20including%20security%20challenges%20and%20priorities.%20As%20neighbours%2C%20we%20need%20to%20collaborate%20closely%20to%20address%20these%20challenges%20confronting%20our%20region%2C%20such%20as%20transnational%20crimes%20and%20Humanitarian%20and%20Disaster%20Relief%20situations.%20We%20look%20forward%20to%20engaging%20with%20the%20new%20administration%20in%20the%20Maldives%20with%20all%20these%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBagchi%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Indian%20prime%20minister%20had%20been%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfirst%20leader%E2%80%9D%20to%20congratulate%20Muizzu%20on%20his%20victory%20on%20Sunday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet%20me%20take%20the%20opportunity%20to%20congratulate%20the%20Maldivian%20people%20for%20once%20again%20demonstrating%20their%20faith%20in%20democratic%20governance%20and%20constitutional%20processes%20that%20reflect%20their%20firm%20commitment%20to%20the%20values%20of%20democracy%20and%20rule%20of%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20high%20commissioner%20Munu%20Mahawar%20called%20on%20the%20president-elect%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20also%20handed%20over%20a%20letter%20from%20the%20Indian%20leader.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20had%20a%20good%20discussion%20on%20various%20aspects%20of%20our%20bilateral%20partnership%2C%20including%20development%20cooperation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20MEA%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20president-elect%E2%80%99s%20office%20had%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F85103%5C%22%3Ereadout%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20discussions%20in%20Mal%C3%A9%20that%20Muizzu%20had%20said%20that%20he%20hoped%20to%20%E2%80%9Crestore%20relations%20with%20India%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20respect%20for%20sovereignty%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMuizzu%2C%20as%20per%20his%20office%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Maldivian%20people%20had%20voted%20in%20the%20presidential%20election%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20sovereignty%2C%20and%20expressed%20confidence%20India%20will%20respect%20the%20decision%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20repayment%20of%20loans%20taken%20by%20the%20Solih%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAssuring%20that%20India%20will%20fully%20respect%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20independence%20and%20sovereignty%2C%20Mahawar%20responded%20that%20New%20Delhi%20was%20ready%20to%20negotiate%20debt%20repayment%2C%20according%20to%20the%20president-elect%E2%80%99s%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.mv%2Fnews%2F29480%5C%22%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EMihaaru%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Muizzu%20said%20that%20the%20most%20pressing%20issue%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20resolved%20once%20he%20assumes%20office%20is%20his%20country%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20issues%20listed%20were%20the%20large%20debt%20owed%20to%20India%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20Indian%20troops%20in%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20foreign%20troops%2C%20we%20do%20not%20have%20any%20problems.%20If%20we%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20speak%20for%20ourselves%20in%20the%20affairs%20of%20our%20country%20and%20what%20our%20country%20has%20to%20say%20on%20other%20platforms%20in%20the%20world%2C%20then%20we%20would%20not%20have%20issues%20with%20any%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Muizzu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Solih%20administration%20had%20repeatedly%20denied%20that%20there%20was%20any%20Indian%20military%20activity%20in%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20the%20large%20projects%20funded%20by%20India%2C%20he%20said%20that%20there%20were%20no%20issues%20as%20long%20as%20there%20were%20no%20military%20personnel%20posted%20in%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20example%2C%20when%20the%20Hanimaadhoo%20Airport%20is%20built%2C%20there%20will%20be%20engineers%20there.%20But%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20be%20%5BIndian%5D%20soldiers.%20Being%20a%20soldier%20is%20the%20problem.%20We%20have%20to%20ask%20them%20to%20sort%20it%20out.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20sorted%20out.%20Civilians%20have%20to%20be%20there%20to%20work.%20Even%20if%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20wear%20the%20uniform%2C%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20there%20are%20military%20personnel%2C%E2%80%9D%20Muizzu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Maldivian%20outlet%20also%20asked%20Muizzu%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-biggest-stakeholder-indian-ocean-region-advisor-muizzu%5C%22%3Eabout%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20quoted%20his%20foreign%20affairs%20adviser%20Mohammed%20Hussain%20Shareef%20%E2%80%98Mundhu%E2%80%99%20as%20saying%20that%20the%20first%20foreign%20visit%20would%20be%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20his%20remarks%2C%20Muizzue%20told%20%3Cem%3EMihaaru%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ENews%3C%2Fem%3E%20t