because%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Enotorious%20unwillingness%20on%20the%20part%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20subaltern%20masses%20to%20follow%20the%20museum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20cultural%20script%E2%80%9D%20by%20transforming%20the%20event%20of%20the%20visit%20into%20an%20entertainment%20as%20well%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3Edarsan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20dialogue%20between%20the%20innumerable%20deities%20on%20display%20and%20the%20devotee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuseums%20in%20India%20are%20identified%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esubaltern%20masses%E2%80%9D%20as%20places%20of%20wonder%20or%20magic%2C%20the%20Ajaib%20Ghar%20made%20famous%20in%20Rudyard%20Kipling%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20%3Cem%3EKim%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20the%20immensely%20popular%20tourist%20destination%20of%20the%20masses%2C%20the%20Jadu%20Ghar%20or%20Indian%20Museum%2C%20where%20thousands%20visit%20en%20route%20to%20the%20pilgrimage%20at%20Ganga%20Sagar%20in%20the%20Sundarban%20or%20political%20rallies%20in%20Kolkata.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20incomplete%20complex%20%E2%80%93%20the%20final%20part%20was%20to%20be%20constructed%20in%202017%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20the%20National%20Museum%20today%20on%20the%20intersection%20of%20erstwhile%20Rajpath-Janpath%20roads%20is%20waiting%20to%20be%20demolished%20as%20the%20plan%20for%20the%20central%20vista%20includes%20its%20erasure.%20Why%20a%20building%2C%20one%20part%20of%20which%20was%20completed%20in%201960%20and%20the%20second%20part%20in%201989%20needs%20to%20be%20destroyed%20is%20unclear.%20The%20venerable%20Indian%20Museum%20building%20in%20Kolkata%20was%20constructed%20and%20opened%20in%201878.%20It%20is%20the%20ninth%20oldest%20museum%20in%20the%20world%20and%20Asia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20first%20museum.%20The%20British%20Museum%20building%20was%20completed%20in%201852.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124130%2FIndia_national_museum_01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124130%2FIndia_national_museum_01.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124130%2FIndia_national_museum_01-300x189.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124130%2FIndia_national_museum_01-1024x644.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678386%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22755%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENational%20Museum%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reported%20demolition%20and%20the%20plan%20to%20make%20a%20museum%20out%20of%20North%20and%20South%20Blocks%20%E2%80%93%20purpose%20built%20offices%20for%20the%20imperial%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20after%201947%2C%20of%20the%20new%20republic%20%E2%80%93%20by%20March%202025%20is%20bizarre.%20There%20is%20no%20logic%20to%20the%20upheaval%3B%20a%20purpose%20built%20museum%20will%20be%20demolished%20and%20two%20purpose%20built%20offices%20%E2%80%93%20North%20and%20South%20will%20be%20emptied%20to%20become%20the%20Yuge%20Yugeen%20Bharat%20Indian%20Museum.%20Buildings%20have%20histories%20and%20demolition%20is%20a%20brutal%20erasure%20that%20rashly%20overwrites%20the%20past.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Thakurta%20asked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhat%20is%20the%20announced%20reason%20behind%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%201960%20building%20of%20the%20National%20Museum%20and%20the%20placing%C2%A0at%20immense%20risk%20of%20all%20the%20irreplaceable%20archaeological%20and%20art%20historical%20artefacts%20that%20it%20houses%3F%20It%20is%20a%C2%A0public%20institution%2C%20always%20intended%20to%20be%20one%2C%20and%C2%A0every%20government%20stands%20obliged%20to%20hold%20these%20objects%20in%20safe%20and%20professional%20custody%20for%20the%20nation%20and%20for%20posterity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20363px)%2085vw%2C%20363px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124111%2FNational-Museum-Delhi-300x225.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22363%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124111%2FNational-Museum-Delhi-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124111%2FNational-Museum-Delhi.jpg%20780w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678385%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22272%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EArtefacts%20on%20display%20in%20the%20museum.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reported%20timeline%20is%20irresponsible.%20The%20National%20Museum%20has%20two%20lakh%20artefacts%2C%20most%20of%20which%20are%20priceless%20and%20a%20part%20of%20not%20only%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20heritage%20and%20identity%20but%20world%20heritage%20too.%20Anyone%20who%20has%20ever%20moved%20a%20modest%20household%20could%20tell%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Culture%20the%20impossibility%20of%20vacating%20a%20premises%20with%20two%20lakh%20objects%20within%20weeks%2C%20because%20the%20deadline%20to%20empty%20out%20the%20existing%20National%20Museum%20buildings%20has%20been%20set%20for%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20took%20the%20British%20Museum%20two%20years%20to%20declutter%2C%20revamp%20and%20refurbish%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESir%20Joseph%20Hotung%20Gallery%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0and%20South%20Asia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20its%202000%20objects%20housed%20in%20a%20115%20meters%20long%20gallery%2C%20because%20such%20displacements%20pose%20serious%20curatorial%20challenges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20Culture%20Secretary%20Jawhar%20Sircar%20has%20been%20asking%20for%20details%20ever%20since%20the%20central%20vista%20plan%20was%20unveiled.%20He%20said%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20received%20only%20evasive%20replies%2C%E2%80%9D%20to%20questions%20on%20if%20a%20tender%20has%20been%20called%20to%20find%20a%20firm%20that%20will%20handle%20the%20packing%20and%20storage%20of%20the%20two%20lakh%20objects%3F%20Common%20sense%20suggests%20that%20invaluable%20artefacts%20cannot%20be%20simply%20packed%20and%20shoved%20into%20storage.%20Specialists%2C%20of%20all%20the%20different%20categories%20of%20artefacts%20in%20the%20National%20Museum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20collection%2C%20have%20to%20be%20identified%20and%20vetted%20and%20then%20allowed%20to%20do%20the%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentral-vista-redevelopment-national-museum-archives-heritage%5C%22%3EIn%20Central%20Vista%20Redevelopment%2C%20the%20Fate%20of%20Our%20Heritage%20Hangs%20in%20Balance%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENational%20Museum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20priceless%20artefacts%20cannot%20be%20put%20into%20just%20any%20warehouse%20or%20even%20a%20storage%20complex.%20Such%20artefacts%20need%20maximum%20security%20to%20ensure%20that%20what%20goes%20in%20can%20be%20retrieved%20intact%20and%20authentic.%20Across%20the%20world%2C%20there%20are%20secretive%2C%20super%20secure%2C%20special%20buildings%20that%20house%20priceless%20artefacts%20and%20art%20works%20in%20transit%20from%20auction%20houses%2C%20private%20sales%20and%20to%20their%20final%20destinations.%20Most%20of%20these%20storages%2C%20like%20the%20Headquarters%20building%20in%20Geneva%20Free%20Port%2C%20are%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20large%20windowless%20concrete%20blocks%20surrounded%20by%20barbed-wire%20fences%2C%20designed%20to%20resist%20earthquakes%20and%20fires.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20buildings%20on%20the%20inside%20have%20several%20rooms%20that%20follow%20specific%20criteria%20to%20fit%20the%20highest%20conservation%20conditions.%20Artworks%20and%20antiquities%20are%20stored%20in%20moisture%20and%20temperature-controlled%20rooms%20conceived%20as%20impenetrable%20safes.%20They%20are%20locked%20behind%20nameless%2C%20armoured%20doors%20built%20to%20hold%20out%20against%20explosives%20and%20equipped%20with%20biometric%20readers%20granting%20access%20to%20only%20the%20legally%20authorised%20few.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20absence%20of%20details%20and%20unsatisfactory%20replies%20to%20Sircar%20suggest%20that%20the%20entire%20business%20of%20packing%20up%20and%20storing%20the%20National%20Museum%20is%20opaque.%20Sircar%20said%20that%20he%20had%20been%20pursuing%20the%20matter%20and%20every%20time%20he%20felt%20he%20was%20being%20fobbed%20off%20with%20replies%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eno%20firm%20decision%20has%20been%20taken.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20333px)%2085vw%2C%20333px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124806%2FScreenshot-2023-10-05-at-12.46.57-PM-1-300x280.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22333%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124806%2FScreenshot-2023-10-05-at-12.46.57-PM-1-300x280.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05124806%2FScreenshot-2023-10-05-at-12.46.57-PM-1.jpg%201013w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678390%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22311%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20jade%20circular%20plate%20on%20display.%20Photo%3A%20nationalmuseumindia.gov.in%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuseums%20in%20India%20loan%20artefacts%20for%20exhibitions%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20and%20overseas.%20These%20are%20small%20bundles%20of%20objects%20for%20which%20there%20are%20obviously%20specialists%20who%20can%20handle%20the%20packing%20and%20shipping.%20But%20packing%20up%20two%20lakh%20artefacts%20is%20an%20entirely%20different%20business.%20The%20storage%20is%20equally%20problematic.%20In%20the%20context%20of%20the%20National%20Museum%2C%20as%20Singh%20had%20pointed%20out%20in%20the%20lecture%20series%20%E2%80%98Modern%20Art%20for%20a%20New%20Nation%E2%80%99%20curated%20by%20Thakurta%2C%20many%20of%20its%20best%20objects%20are%20loans%20from%20museums%20as%20distant%20as%20the%20British%20Museum%20in%20London%2C%20the%20Patna%20Museum%2C%20the%20Chennai%20Museum%20and%20the%20Indian%20Museum%20in%20Kolkata.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20national%20treasures%2C%20the%20safekeeping%20of%20which%20has%20been%20given%20to%20the%20officials%20of%20the%20National%20Museum%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Culture%20and%20therefore%20by%20extension%20to%20the%20government%20headed%20by%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20citizens%20have%20a%20right%20to%20be%20informed%2C%20in%20detail%20and%20with%20transparency%2C%20how%20this%20near%20impossible%20task%20will%20be%20executed.%20Thakurta%20questioned%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EDoes%20this%20government%20have%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eany%20legal%20right%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0to%20meddle%20with%20institutions%C2%A0like%20the%20National%20Museum%20and%20the%20National%20Archives%20and%20endanger%20the%20historical%20inheritance%C2%A0of%20the%20people%20of%20India%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDemolishing%20the%20National%20Museum%20because%20it%20is%20aged%20and%20infirm%2C%20even%20though%20it%20is%20a%20mere%2060%20years%20old%20is%20one%20thing.%20Housing%20it%20in%20the%20North%20and%20South%20Blocks%2C%20which%20are%20even%20older%20and%20considered%20unsafe%2C%20because%20they%20are%20not%20earthquake%20proof%20seems%20incredibly%20silly.%20More%20so%2C%20because%20as%20Sircar%20pointed%20out%20museums%20need%20enormously%20strong%20load%20bearing%20walls%2C%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20artefacts%20are%20very%20heavy%20indeed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20decision%20is%20irrational.%20Thakurta%E2%80%99s%20dismay%20is%20evident%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20terrifying%20is%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Culture%E2%80%99s%20complete%20silence%2C%20evasiveness%20and%20lack%20of%20any%20clarity%20about%20why%20the%20current%20complex%20must%20be%20demolished%20and%20moved%20to%20completely%20unsuitable%20locations%20like%20the%20office%20buildings%20of%20the%20North%20and%20South%20Block.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentral-vista-project-demolition%5C%22%3EA%20Demolition%20Drive%20Called%20the%20Central%20Vista%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20original%20design%20for%20the%20National%20Museum%20was%20for%20a%20complex%20with%20three%20parts.%20The%20first%20was%20the%20main%20building%20inaugurated%20by%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20the%20second%20was%20opened%20in%201989.%20The%20foundation%20stone%20for%20the%20third%20part%20was%20laid%20on%20December%2018%2C%202017.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20National%20Museum%20%E2%80%9Cis%20also%20already%20part%20of%20a%20well-conceived%20cultural%20complex%20that%20was%20conceived%20by%20the%20builders%20of%20New%20Delhi%20to%20sit%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20Rajpath-Janpath%20artery%20of%20the%20capital%E2%80%9D%20Thakurta%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGrace%20Morley%2C%20the%20National%20Museum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20first%20director%2C%20took%20four%20years%20to%20decide%20which%20objects%20would%20be%20displayed%20and%20how.%20She%20was%20invited%20by%20the%20government%20of%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20to%20do%20this%2C%20having%20worked%20as%20the%20director%20of%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Museum%20of%20Art%20before%20she%20came%20to%20India.%20As%20an%20advocate%20of%20cultural%20democracy%20she%20ensured%20that%20the%20display%20design%20of%20the%20National%20Museum%20reflects%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esecularisation%20and%20democratisation%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20presentation%20of%20sculptures%20in%20white%20cube%20spaces%20with%20minimal%20contextual%20information.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05125612%2FScreenshot-2023-10-05-at-12.55.51-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05125612%2FScreenshot-2023-10-05-at-12.55.51-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05125612%2FScreenshot-2023-10-05-at-12.55.51-PM-300x200.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05125612%2FScreenshot-2023-10-05-at-12.55.51-PM-1024x680.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-678393%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22797%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGrace%20Morley%20with%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru.%20Photo%3A%20National%20Museum%2C%20New%20Delhi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20very%20good%20reason%20for%20the%20way%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENational%20Museum%20displayed%20its%20collection.%20It%20was%20to%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecelebrate%20the%20ancient%20culture%20of%20a%20young%20state%20%E2%80%9D%20as%20Singh%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Idea%20of%20a%20National%20Museum%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ean%20act%20of%20great%20symbolic%20importance.%E2%80%9D%20It%20was%20within%20this%20structure%20that%20India%20believed%20it%20could%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eshare%20its%20masterpieces%20with%20its%20citizens%20in%20a%20symbolic%20affirmation%20of%20their%20rights.%E2%80%9D%20It%20also%20narrated%20through%20the%20materiality%20of%20stone%2C%20particularly%20sculpture%2C%20a%20nationalist%20history%2C%20according%20to%20Singh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETracing%20the%20connect%20between%20archaeology%20and%20the%20analytical%20framework%20Thakurta%20argued%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehistory%20was%20not%20always%20extracted%20from%20stone%2C%20rather%20stone%20became%20the%20proof%20of%20a%20preconceived%20historical%20cycle.%20The%20demolition%20of%20the%20National%20Museum%20building%20raises%20the%20question%2C%20is%20it%20the%20stone%20that%20offends%20a%20specific%20preconceived%20historical%20cycle%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuseums%20in%20India%20have%20generally%20not%20been%20careful%20with%20priceless%20artefacts.%20The%20revamp%20of%20the%20Indian%20Museum%20caused%20breakages%20of%20the%202000-year-old%20Mauryan%20sculpture%2C%20the%20Yakshi%20guarding%20the%20doors%20to%20the%20Bharhut%20gallery.%20The%203%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20century%20BC%20Lion%20Capital%20was%20damaged%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Museum%20in%20its%20present%20location%20in%20New%20Delhi%20is%20national.%20It%20belongs%20to%20the%20generations%20of%20visitors%20who%20spent%20time%20in%20it.%20The%20building%2C%20its%20location%2C%20its%20design%20and%20its%20artefacts%20on%20display%20tell%20the%20story%20of%20the%20nation%20as%20it%20was%20imagined%20at%20birth%2C%20inclusive%2C%20accessible%20and%20democratic.%20The%20deliberate%20dislocation%20cancels%20the%20story%20of%20version%201.0%20of%20India%20when%20it%20was%20in%20its%20infancy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fshikha-mukerjee%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EShikha%20Mukherjee%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Kolkata-based%20commentator.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696505416000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05123902%2F2268292509_c6a540e595_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fthe-demolition-of-the-national-museum-will-extinguish-the-identity-of-an-india-that-was-born-in-1947%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20logic%20behind%20breaking%20down%20the%20present%20structure%20and%20shifting%20the%20nearly%20two%20lakh%20artefacts%20to%20North%20and%20South%20Blocks.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A60%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fthe-demolition-of-the-national-museum-will-extinguish-the-identity-of-an-india-that-was-born-in-1947%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Not%20My%20Lawyer%E2%80%99%3A%20Urmilesh%20Rebuts%20Claims%20of%20Man%20Identified%20as%20His%20Advocate%20in%20News%20Reports%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F11071727%2FUrmilesh.00_22_05_13.Still003.jpg%5C%22