0amongst%20various%20sections%20of%20society%E2%80%9D%20including%20creating%20%E2%80%9Ca%20false%20narrative%20%E2%80%A6%20to%20discredit%20the%20efforts%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20contain%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%E2%80%9D.%20Second%2C%20the%20police%20claim%20that%20%E2%80%9Csecret%20inputs%20revealed%20%E2%80%A6%20(Neville%20Roy%20Singham%20and%20Purkayastha)%20exchanged%20emails%20which%20expose%20their%20intent%20to%20show%20Kashmir%20and%20Arunachal%20is%20not%20part%20of%20India%20%E2%80%A6%20(thus)%20undermining%20the%20unity%20and%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%9D.%20The%20third%20charge%20against%20the%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20journalists%20is%20their%20friendship%20with%20Gautam%20Navlakha%20since%201991%20and%20the%20fact%20he%20is%20a%20shareholder%20of%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20since%20its%20inception%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBaru%20also%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Ca%20sad%20day%E2%80%9D%20that%20no%20editor%20of%20any%20major%20newspaper%20or%20major%20news%20channel%20was%20present%20at%20the%20protest%20held%20at%20the%20Press%20Club%20of%20India%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FsLnD7hqkarU%3Fsi%3D-sqDbzoSeYvLKfyZ%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20transcript%20of%20the%20interview%20is%20being%20prepared%20and%20will%20be%20published%20when%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696494177000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F05135024%2FKT-5-October.00_26_11_08.Still002.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fwatch-raids-on-46-journalists-intimidation-reminiscent-of-emergency-charges-against-newsclick-laughable%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sanjaya%20Baru%2C%20a%20former%20editor%20of%20Business%20Standard%20and%20former%20media%20advisor%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20says%20the%20scale%20of%20this%20operation%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20sign%20of%20incompetence%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20police.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fwatch-raids-on-46-journalists-intimidation-reminiscent-of-emergency-charges-against-newsclick-laughable%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222023%20on%20Track%20to%20Become%20Hottest%20Year%20Ever%20Recorded%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F04114758%2FHeat-wave-illustration.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20is%20set%20to%20become%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fun-warns-of-climate-breakdown-after-record-heat%2Fa-66731587%5C%22%3Ehottest%20year%20ever%20recorded%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20last%20month%20being%20the%20warmest%20September%20on%20record%2C%20according%20to%20a%C2%A0report%20by%20the%20European%20Union%E2%80%99s%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%20(C3S).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20found%20that%20the%20global%20temperature%20for%20January-September%202023%20was%200.52%20degrees%20Celsius%20(0.9%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%20higher%20than%20average.%20It%20was%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fjuly-2023-was-the-hottest-month-ever-recorded-eu-confirms%2Fa-66467143%5C%22%3Ehotter%20than%20the%20first%20nine%20months%20of%20the%20warmest%20calendar%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202016%2C%20by%200.05%C2%A0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20mean%20temperature%20so%20far%20this%20year%20is%201.40%20C%C2%A0higher%20than%20the%20preindustrial%20average%20between%201850%20and%201900.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20sense%20of%20urgency%20for%20ambitious%20climate%20action%20has%20never%20been%20more%20critical%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Samantha%20Burgess%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20C3S%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20release%20comes%20just%20two%20months%20ahead%20of%20UN%20climate%20talks%20in%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EScientists%20say%20climate%20change%20caused%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20is%20making%20extreme%20weather%20such%20as%20heat%20waves%20and%20storms%20more%20intense%20and%20frequent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20the%20report%20say%20about%20September%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%C2%A0the%20report%2C%20September%202023%20was%20the%20warmest%20September%20on%20record.%20Average%20surface%20air%20temperature%20reached%2016.38%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20which%20is%200.93%20C%C2%A0above%20the%20monthly%20average%20during%201991-2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%200.5%20C%C2%A0warmer%20than%20the%20previous%20warmest%20September%20to%20date%2C%20in%202020.%20That%20month%20was%20roughly%201.75%20C%C2%A0warmer%20than%20the%20September%20average%20of%20the%20preindustrial%20reference%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20unprecedented%20temperatures%20for%20the%20time%20of%20year%20observed%20in%20September%20%E2%80%93%20following%20a%20record%20summer%20%E2%80%93%20have%20broken%20records%20by%20an%20extraordinary%20amount%2C%E2%80%9D%20Burgess%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20described%20the%20month%20as%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%E2%80%9D%2C%20crediting%20it%20for%20pushing%202023%20%E2%80%9Cinto%20the%20dubious%20honour%20of%20first%20place%20%E2%80%93%20on%20track%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20year%20and%20around%201.4%20C%20above%20preindustrial%20average%20temperatures.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Wetter-than-average%E2%80%99%20September%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Europe%2C%20the%20month%20was%20not%20only%20the%20hottest%20on%20record%20but%20also%20one%20with%20%E2%80%9Cwetter-than-average%E2%80%9D%20conditions%20along%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20continent%E2%80%99s%20western%20seaboard%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fclimate-change-fueled-flooding-in-libya-greece-bulgaria-study%2Fa-66862911%5C%22%3Ecited%20the%20extreme%20rainfall%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20Greece%2C%20associated%20with%20Storm%20Daniel.%20The%20storm%20also%20caused%20devastating%20flooding%20in%20Libya%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Flibya-thousands-feared-dead-after-storm-daniel%2Fa-66783443%5C%22%3Ekilling%20thousands%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20largely%20destroying%20its%20eastern%20city%20of%20Derna.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20areas%20affected%20by%20rain%20in%20Europe%20include%C2%A0the%20western%20Iberian%20Peninsula%2C%20Ireland%2C%20northern%20Britain%2C%20and%20Scandinavia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBeyond%20Europe%2C%20the%20Latin%20American%20countries%20of%20Brazil%20and%20Chile%20also%20experienced%20what%20the%20report%20said%20were%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%20precipitation%20events%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20the%20countries%E2%80%99%20southern%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20C3S%20is%20implemented%20by%20the%20European%20Center%20for%20Medium-Range%20Weather%20Forecasts%20on%20Behalf%20of%20the%20European%20Commission.%20It%20is%20funded%20by%20the%20EU.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20service%20said%20the%20findings%20are%20all%20based%20on%20computer-generated%20analyses%2C%20using%20measurements%20from%20satellites%2C%20ships%2C%20aircraft%20and%20weather%20stations%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2F2023-on-track-to-be-hottest-year-on-record%2Fa-66999709%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696493955000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F06%2F04114